oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Cumberland Mountain State Park bridge
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of a partially completed bridge at Cumberland Mountain State Park. A young man stands on the frozen creek, center. There is snow on the ground and the construction is shown in the background. From 1935 to 1938 Company 3464 of the Civilian Conservation Corps (CCC) built a stone masonry bridge and dam out of local Crab Orchard stone to create Byrd's Lake as the park's central focus.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:coverage: Crossville (Tenn.); Cumberland Mountain State Park (Tenn.); Cumberland County (Tenn.)
